g.title: j572398634
g.text: What do you do for hobbies out there in space? In the future?

g.title: j3293909235
g.text: What do you do for fun?

g.title: j4172962412
g.text: Oops! There's a bee in here! BRB! [End.]

g.title: j471271364
g.text: So sue me for showing a little interest in *you* for a change.

g.title: j1037340320
g.text: Nothing. I died a lot. Thanks for reminding me. [End.]

g.title: j3730233319
g.text: Well... reading. I did a lot of reading.

g.title: j898359690
g.text: The stories I kept in my head were the only things I was allowed to keep on Duviri.

g.title: j4267927964
g.text: Everything else would disappear when it looped.

g.title: j3704505019
g.text: And when I was alone on the Zariman, the people on the page were the only friends I had.

g.title: j4281708647
g.text: Now? I play games with Ordis. And read. And... still keep to myself, really.

g.title: j2660936461
g.text: I ate the square spaghetti, Arthur. That is a LIE.

g.title: j225107490
g.text: What I'm trying to say is - would you like to learn to cook? It's a great hobby.

g.title: j3326986604
g.text: LOOK. I said I was sorry!

g.title: j2445322344
g.text: Are you offering to loan me a book?

g.title: j4154606823
g.text: No, daftie. I'm offering to teach you.

g.title: j297149175
g.text: I'd love that. But can you wear one of those cute aprons? And.... maybe only the apron? ;)
